        <p>The bathroom is the first space you visit when waking up and the last before sleeping. It's your personal sanctuary, where you prepare to face the day and relax after an intense day. A well-designed bathroom not only improves your quality of life but adds real value to your property and prevents costly moisture and leakage problems.</p>

        <p>At ReformaT Houston we have been remodeling bathrooms in Houston, The Woodlands, Sugar Land, and Katy for over 20 years. We know the particularities of Texas homes: pipes that require maintenance, waterproofing that needs reinforcement, and water pressure issues. Each project addresses these challenges with professional and lasting solutions.</p>

        <img src="/images/bathrooms-800.webp" alt="Modern bathroom completely finished by ReformaT Houston with premium finishes and spa design" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" />

        <h2>Waterproofing: The Foundation of Every Durable Bathroom</h2>

        <p>In Texas, humidity is the number one enemy of bathrooms. Intense rains, high ambient humidity, and constructions with deficient waterproofing create the perfect scenario for leaks, mold, and structural damage. Poorly executed waterproofing can cause problems on lower floors, damage furniture, and create unhealthy environments.</p>

        <h3>Our Professional Waterproofing System</h3>

        <p><strong>Step 1: Surface preparation.</strong> We completely remove old coating until reaching block or concrete. We clean, level, and repair cracks with structural repair mortar. We apply primer to guarantee perfect adhesion.</p>

        <p><strong>Step 2: First waterproofing layer.</strong> We apply high-elasticity liquid membrane on walls and floor, completely covering all surfaces. This layer is flexible and supports structural movements without cracking.</p>

        <p><strong>Step 3: Reinforcement at critical points.</strong> In corners, wall-floor joints, and around drains, we apply reinforcing mesh embedded in the membrane. These are the points where 90% of leaks occur.</p>

        <p><strong>Step 4: Second waterproofing layer.</strong> We apply a second layer perpendicular to the first, creating a double barrier. We let it cure according to humidity and temperature conditions.</p>

        <p><strong>Step 5: Watertightness test.</strong> Before placing tiles, we verify there are no leaks. Only after passing this test do we continue with cladding.</p>

        <p><strong>Warranty:</strong> We offer waterproofing warranty. If there is any leak, we repair it at no cost.</p>

        <h2>Spa-Type Design in Your Home</h2>

        <p>Modern bathrooms have evolved from being purely functional spaces to becoming relaxation sanctuaries. We design bathrooms that combine technology, comfort, and aesthetics to create complete sensory experiences.</p>

        <h3>Floor-Level Showers</h3>

        <p>Walk-in showers without trays are the dominant trend in premium bathrooms. We eliminate the traditional step, creating an open and accessible space. The floor has a minimum slope towards the linear drain, guaranteeing perfect water evacuation without flooding.</p>

        <p><strong>Advantages:</strong> Minimalist aesthetics, easy cleaning (no corners where dirt accumulates), accessible for people with reduced mobility, sense of visual amplitude.</p>

        <p><strong>Technical considerations:</strong> Requires perfect waterproofing, high-capacity linear drain, tempered glass enclosure with anti-lime treatment.</p>

        <h3>Freestanding Tubs</h3>

        <p>For those who prefer the experience of an immersion bath, freestanding tubs are sculptural pieces that become the focal point of the bathroom. Available in acrylic, composite resin, or natural stone.</p>

        <p><strong>Popular types:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Modern oval tubs:</strong> Clean and minimalist lines.</li>
          <li><strong>Clawfoot tubs:</strong> Elegant vintage style.</li>
          <li><strong>Natural stone tubs:</strong> Carved marble or granite.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Finishes: Aesthetics and Functionality</h2>

        <p>Tiles and finishes define the visual character of the bathroom and must fulfill technical functions: water resistance, ease of cleaning, durability, and safety (non-slip on floors).</p>

        <h3>Large Format Porcelain Tiles</h3>

        <p>The current trend is large-format pieces. Fewer joints mean less maintenance and a cleaner look. Available in finishes that imitate marble, wood, concrete, and natural stone with surprising realism.</p>

        <p><strong>Advantages:</strong> Premium aesthetics, easy cleaning, extreme durability, resistance to stains and chemicals.</p>

        <h2>Faucets: Where Quality Shows</h2>

        <p>Faucets are one of the most used elements in a bathroom. Quality faucets last years, while cheap ones can fail prematurely. Investing in good faucets is investing in peace of mind.</p>

        <h3>Brands We Recommend</h3>

        <p><strong>Grohe (Germany):</strong> Bright chrome plating technology that doesn't scratch, ceramic cartridges, water saving.</p>

        <p><strong>Hansgrohe (Germany):</strong> Technology that mixes air with water for softer drops, intuitive control, more space under the faucet.</p>

        <p><strong>Moen (USA):</strong> Excellent quality-price ratio, modern designs, easily available spare parts in Houston.</p>

        <h2>Lighting and Mirrors</h2>

        <p>Correct lighting transforms a functional bathroom into a luxury space. We design systems that combine general, task, and decorative lighting.</p>

        <h3>Task Lighting (Essential)</h3>

        <p>Lights on both sides of the mirror (not above) that illuminate the face without creating shadows. Neutral color temperature that faithfully reproduces colors, essential for makeup and shaving.</p>

        <p><strong>Options:</strong> LED side sconces, mirrors with integrated LED, LED strips behind the mirror (halo effect).</p>

        <h2>Toilets: Comfort and Efficiency</h2>

        <p>Modern toilets consume less water than old models and offer functions that significantly improve the user experience.</p>

        <h3>Wall-Hung Toilets</h3>

        <p>They install on the wall, leaving the floor completely free. They facilitate cleaning, create a sense of amplitude, and have minimalist design.</p>

        <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> Support structure embedded in wall (hidden tank), adequate wall thickness or structural reinforcement.</p>

        <p><strong>Recommended brands:</strong> Geberit, Grohe, Toto.</p>

        <h2>Ventilation: Prevention of Humidity and Mold</h2>

        <p>Adequate ventilation is crucial in Texas bathrooms due to high ambient humidity. Without correct ventilation, steam condenses on walls and ceilings, creating mold, damaging paint, and creating unhealthy environments.</p>

        <h3>Air Extractors</h3>

        <p><strong>Required capacity:</strong> Minimum 8 air changes per hour to completely eliminate humidity.</p>

        <p><strong>Types:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Wall extractor:</strong> Installed on exterior wall.</li>
          <li><strong>Ceiling extractor:</strong> For bathrooms without exterior wall, duct to roof.</li>
          <li><strong>Humidity sensor extractor:</strong> Activates automatically when detecting steam.</li>
          <li><strong>Silent extractor:</strong> Less than 30 decibels (doesn't disturb during bath).</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Extractor with timer that continues running after turning off the light, completely eliminating residual humidity.</p>

        <h2>The Bathroom Remodel Process</h2>

        <h3>Phase 1: Consultation and Advice</h3>
        <p>We visit your home in Houston, The Woodlands, Sugar Land, or Katy, evaluate the current state of the bathroom (pipes, waterproofing, ventilation), take precise measurements, and listen to your needs. We create design proposals with technical plans.</p>

        <h3>Phase 2: Design and Budget</h3>
        <p>We elaborate detailed budget including: demolition, waterproofing, plumbing, electricity, coatings, sanitary ware, faucets, lighting, and final cleaning. We sign contract with dates and warranty.</p>

        <h3>Phase 3: Preparation and Materials</h3>
        <p>We prepare all necessary materials and coordinate with suppliers. We protect existing areas and establish work schedule.</p>

        <h3>Phase 4: Execution</h3>
        <p>Our team executes the work following established phases: demolition, infrastructure, waterproofing, coatings, installations, and finishes.</p>

        <h3>Phase 5: Delivery</h3>
        <p>Thorough inspection with you, deep cleaning, and explanation of care and maintenance. Warranty documentation delivery.</p>

